
[1]palmistry

   PAL'MISTRY, n. [L. palma, palm.] The art or practice of divining or
   telling fortunes by the lines and marks in the palm of the hand; a
   trick of imposture, much practiced by gypsies.

   1. Addison used it humorously for the action of the hand.
